trans-unit.source:
\n

Specifies the data types to use when storing values in the registry, or identifies the data type of a value in the registry.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxxxxxxx xxx xxxx xxxxx xx xxx xxxx xxxxxxx xxxxxx xx xxx xxxxxxxx$ xx xxxxxxxxxx xxx xxxx xxxx xx x xxxxx xx xxx xxxxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
This value is equivalent to the Win32 API registry data type REG_BINARY.

\n
trans-unit.target: Xxxx xxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxx xx xxx Xxx00 XXX xxxxxxxx xxxx xxxx XXX$XXXXXX.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
This value is equivalent to the Win32 API registry data type REG_DWORD.

\n
trans-unit.target: Xxxx xxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxx xx xxx Xxx00 XXX xxxxxxxx xxxx xxxx XXX$XXXXX.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

A null-terminated string that contains unexpanded references to environment variables, such as %PATH%, that are expanded when the value is retrieved.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$X xxxx$xxxxxxxxxx xxxxxx xxxx xxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx$ xxxx xx $XXXX$$ xxxx xxx xxxxxxxx xxxx xxx xxxxx xx xxxxxxxxx.

trans-unit.source:
This value is equivalent to the Win32 API registry data type REG_EXPAND_SZ.

\n
trans-unit.target: Xxxx xxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxx xx xxx Xxx00 XXX xxxxxxxx xxxx xxxx XXX$XXXXXX$XX.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

An array of null-terminated strings, terminated by two null characters.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xx xxxxx xx xxxx$xxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxx$ xxxxxxxxxx xx xxx xxxx xxxxxxxxxx.

trans-unit.source:
This value is equivalent to the Win32 API registry data type REG_MULTI_SZ.

\n
trans-unit.target: Xxxx xxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxx xx xxx Xxx00 XXX xxxxxxxx xxxx xxxx XXX$XXXXX$XX.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
This value is equivalent to the Win32 API registry data type REG_QWORD.

\n
trans-unit.target: Xxxx xxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxx xx xxx Xxx00 XXX xxxxxxxx xxxx xxxx XXX$XXXXX.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
This value is equivalent to the Win32 API registry data type REG_SZ.

\n
trans-unit.target: Xxxx xxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxx xx xxx Xxx00 XXX xxxxxxxx xxxx xxxx XXX$XX.$$x$$x
